President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Nebraska due to severe storms, flooding, and tornadoes that occurred from June 5-26, 2009. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Michael L. Karl has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA.